# D18_SKCM_GDSC2_PHARMACOLOGY_v1
# Pre-registration: GDSC2 pharmacological validation of D17 SKCM structural predictions
# Date: 2026-06-08
# Status: PRE-REGISTERED — do not open GDSC2 SKCM data before this commit

## Scientific background

D17 (pre-reg f61b837) produced two structural pharmacology predictions for TCGA SKCM:
(1) EGFR is a strong structural ANCHOR in BRAF-WT melanoma (z_dr = -3.204), the largest
    cross-cancer structural contrast in the dataset (CRC reference: z = +2.411 DAMPER).
    ANCHOR prediction: EGFR removal INCREASES r(A,B) → EGFR inhibitors should be
    structurally DETRIMENTAL to inter-layer coherence → predicted INEFFECTIVE in melanoma.
(2) SOS1 is the top structural DAMPER in both SKCM groups (z ≈ +3.2), predicting efficacy
    of SOS1 inhibitors (not yet available in GDSC2; a drug discovery gap).

D18 tests these predictions using GDSC2 melanoma (TCGA_DESC = "SKCM", n=54 cell lines):
- Does the EGFR ANCHOR prediction match pharmacology? (H1, H3)
- Does BRAF inhibitor dominance appear (driver addiction override)?
- Is the between-cancer EGFR differential confirmed at pharmacological level? (H4)

This is the melanoma parallel of D15 (CRC GDSC2 pharmacology).
The critical test: D17 found EGFR ANCHOR (z=-3.204) → D18 tests if EGFR inhibitors
rank last in melanoma while BRAF inhibitors rank first.

